Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, March 24 (AFP) -- A bomb explosion wounded 
four people Thursday [24 March] in Istanbul's Grand Bazaar, in 
the heart of the city's historic tourist district, in the second 
such attack in less than a week, police said. 
  They said a Romanian was among the casualties from the blast 
which occurred in a ladies' toilet. 
  On Saturday, an explosion in the Haydarpasa train station 
here left a Singaporian national wounded. 

